HEADWORD: Terrific
<hw>Ter*rif"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>terrificus</ets>; fr. <ets>terrere</ets> to frighten +
<ets>facere</ets> to make. See <er>Terror</er>, and
<er>Fact</er>.]</ety> <def>Causing terror; adapted to excite great fear
or dread; terrible; <as>as, a <ex>terrific</ex> form; a
<ex>terrific</ex> sight.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

